<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Privacy Policy - SKKF App</title>
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=DM+Sans:ital,opsz,wght@0,9..40,400;0,9..40,500;0,9..40,600;0,9..40,700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  <style>
    :root {
      --bg: #f5f6f8;
      --surface: #ffffff;
      --text: #1a1d21;
      --text-muted: #6b7280;
      --primary: #e31837;
      --primary-dark: #b8142c;
      --border: #e5e7eb;
      --radius: 16px;
      --shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
    }
    * { box-sizing: border-box; }
    body {
      font-family: 'DM Sans', system-ui, sans-serif;
      background: var(--bg);
      color: var(--text);
      line-height: 1.65;
      margin: 0;
      min-height: 100vh;
    }
    .container {
      max-width: 680px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 32px 24px 48px;
    }
    .card {
      background: var(--surface);
      border-radius: 24px;
      box-shadow: var(--shadow);
      padding: 40px 36px;
      margin-bottom: 24px;
    }
    .brand {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 12px;
      margin-bottom: 32px;
      padding-bottom: 24px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
    .brand-icon {
      width: 44px;
      height: 44px;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--primary), var(--primary-dark));
      border-radius: 12px;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      color: white;
      font-weight: 700;
      font-size: 16px;
    }
    .brand-text { font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text); }
    h1 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      margin: 0 0 8px;
      color: var(--text);
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    }
    .updated {
      color: var(--text-muted);
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      margin-bottom: 28px;
    }
    h2 {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin: 1.75em 0 0.5em;
      color: var(--text);
    }
    p { margin: 0.5em 0; color: var(--text); }
    ul {
      margin: 0.5em 0;
      padding-left: 1.5em;
      color: var(--text);
    }
    li { margin: 0.35em 0; }
    strong { color: var(--text); }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="brand">
        <div class="brand-icon">S</div>
        <span class="brand-text">SKKF App</span>
      </div>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="updated">Last updated: February 2026</p>

      <p>This privacy policy describes how the SKKF app (“we”, “the app”) handles information when you use the application.</p>

      <h2>1. Information we collect and use</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Account and profile:</strong> When you sign in or create a profile, we store your name, phone number, email (if provided), and date of birth (if provided) in our secure database to provide the app’s services.</li>
        <li><strong>Contacts (Android):</strong> The app can access your device contacts <strong>only when you choose “Pick from contacts”</strong> (e.g. when an admin adds a member). We use this solely to let you select a contact to add; we do not upload or store your full contact list on our servers. You can deny this permission and still use the app by entering details manually.</li>
        <li><strong>Notifications:</strong> If you enable notifications, we store a device token so we can send you relevant alerts (e.g. loan issued, repayment recorded).</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. How we store and protect data</h2>
      <p>Your data is stored using Firebase (Google) services. We do not sell your personal information to third parties.</p>

      <h2>3. Your choices</h2>
      <p>You can revoke contact access in your device settings at any time. You can opt out of notifications in the app or device settings.</p>

      <h2>4. Contact</h2>
      <p>For questions about this privacy policy or your data, contact the app administrator or your organisation.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
